    <note>Gong(2) Huiyuan [10195] YLDD, 2368 has him a jinshi equivalency in 1000 and as Zhi's [10192] nephew. Fujian TZ, 147.12a has him as jinshi in 1030, which makes much more sense chronologically, Moreover Huiyan's listed son, Kuang [10196], jinshi in 1088 is not listed as a Kunshan jinshi, but has the same generational name as Zongyuan's [7114] grandson, Kuang(2) [10198]. Kuang is probably a grandson rather than son, which makes chronological sense and both Huiyuan and Kuang are members of the Shaowu branch (jia=a) of the lineage. Whether or not Huiyuan is a nephew (i.e. son of a brother who remained in Shaowu) or a lineage nephew (i.e. grandson of one of Shenyi's [10192] brothers) is not clear. CBD, 5, 4506.</note>
